   "source": [
    "8 solution:\n",
    "\n",
    "We know that, \n",
    "test-error >= training-error\n",
    "\n",
    "For K Nearest Neighbor (K = 1),\n",
    "0.5*x1 + 0.5*x2 = 0.18\n",
    "x1 = training error rate, x2 = test error rate\n",
    "since x1 <= x2 \n",
    "=> x1 + eps = x2\n",
    "=> 0.5*x1 + 0.5*(x1 + eps) = 0.18\n",
    "=> x1 = 0.18 - 0.5*eps\n",
    "since minimum possible value of x1 = 0 => 0.18 - 0.5*eps = 0\n",
    "=> eps = 0.18/0.5 = 0.36\n",
    "\n",
    "eps is in range [0, 0.36]\n",
    "range of x2 is [0.18, 0.54]\n",
    "\n",
    "But for KNN with K = 1 so every point is it's nearest neighbor hence x1 = 0 => x2 = 0.36\n",
    "so Linear Regression is preferred."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fb16a03f-6a68-489c-9bf6-3f1a2927837d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Modified solution with ChatGPT help:\n",
    "For KNN with K=1, each training observation is its own nearest neighbor, so the training error is approximately zero. Since the average of the training and test errors is 18%, this implies that the test error is approximately 36%. This is larger than the 30% test error obtained using logistic regression. Therefore, logistic regression should be preferred for classifying new observations."
   ]
  }
